<H2><A NAME="does the dbi have a year 2000 problem">Does the DBI have a year 2000 problem?</A></H2>
<P>No. The DBI has no knowledge or understanding of dates at all.</P>
<P>Individual drivers (DBD::*) may have some date handling code but are
unlikely to have year 2000 related problems within their code. However,
your application code which <EM>uses</EM> the DBI and DBD drivers may have
year 2000 related problems if it has not been designed and written well.</P>
<P>See also the ``Does Perl have a year 2000 problem?'' section of the Perl FAQ:</P>
